<br>
Phantasmal Armor (The one that is Phantom Armour, but uses 1 pearl instead of 4 cats eye agates) drops from:<br>
<br>
Magister Sshsomething at Ssra temple in Luclin.<br>
<br>
Magister spawns somewhere near Rhag1 because it was pulled soon after Rhag1 fight when we started going back to zone. So it should be at 1st level in the temple. We have killed Magister twice and gotten some boots once and this spell another time.<br>
<br>
This is the same kind of idea as the VahShir illusion for enchanters that also drop only in that area from one specific rare mob as rare drop.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, the Phantasmal Protection (aka Transos) drops from higher level common snakes in Ssra temple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 821<br> <font color=#333333>(6/13/02 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1339.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Phantasmal Armor</span><hr size=1> Ah, then unlike the Vahshir illusion spell, which is actually usefull to any enchanter going into Ssra, this spell is more or less destroyed on sight due to it's rarity and pointlessness when confronted with it's higher level and more common <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Phantasmal Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell.<br>
